<br>
There's some variables I used numerous times:<br>
x = mana savings <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> (caused by specialization, casting mastery, and mana preservation-type items)</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
y = basic mana regen rate in mana/<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> sec</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> (not mana per tick, and this is here because I made the assumption that if you're not casting a spell you're sitting down and medding, or using that time to rune-med with a Shield of Auras type effect.  I don't exactly know what sitting med rate is - about 4mana/sec I believe.  y does not include any FT items or effects because they are irrelivant to the analysis.  Yours may vary - my rate is about 12mana/sec using SoA)</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
r = cast time reduction <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> (caused by items like Naki ring, or other skills like Quick Summoning)</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
s = normal cast time of a spell<br>
<br>
Remember that if something says 10%, that you have to use 0.10 in the equation.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Mental Clarity</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> - This one's pretty simple.<br>
<br>
(increase in FT) / (points spent)<br>
<br>
So spending 12 total points on Mental Clarity obtains 3 FT, or 0.25 FT/point.  However the first 2 points spent work out to 0.5 FT/point, while the last 6 runs at only 0.167 FT/point.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Innate Regeneration</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> - Using Modrod2<br>
<br>
(660 - (400 * (1 - x)) - (y*((3*0.5) + 4.5*(1-r)))) / 900 / 1 point<br>
<br>
the 3*0.5 is just a approximationn for time takes to actually click the rod 3 times.  The expression containing y means the amount of mana lost because you could have been medding during that time instead.  900 is the number of ticks to get all the health regened back.<br>
<br>
So with just specialization (about 11% mana savings I believe) and rate of 4mana/sec on y, with a 15% reduction using a Naki ring:  (660 - 356 - 21.3) / 900  =  222.7 / 900 = 0.247 FT/point.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Spell Casting Mastery 3</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> - This one rules<br>
<br>
(mana spent per minute) * x / 10 / 12<br>
<br>
10 is the number of ticks in a minute, 12 is number of points for SCM3.  I believe I read tests show SCM3 to be about a 10% savings.<br>
<br>
So lets say you use 1000 base mana in a minute - that's almost exactly 3 cast SoFB.  1000 * 0.10 / 10 / 12 means that by spending 1000 mana in a minute, 100 of it is knocked off by SCM3, meaning about 10 mana per tick saved.  That gives SCM3 and incredible 0.833 FT/point when you're using 1000 mana a minute.  If you're chain making modrods, say 10 a minute, that's 4000 mana used and 400 saved.  Effectively giving you a sustained 40FT during that minute and FT/point ratio over 3 - by far the best of any AA.  Even using as little as 400mana a minute, you get 0.33FT/point However, unlike innate regen and mental clarity, which are always going, this relies on you to be casting to take advantage of it.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Deftness</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> - How many magi actually have this? =p<br>
This one's a bit odd - the flowing thought rate gained by this skill, similar to Quick Summoning, is only active during times when you are casting beneficial spells - this would usually be useful if you solo by healing your pet almost exclusively. (which is I do - pet heal, SoA med, nuke when mana's full - gets me a point in less than 3 hours)<br>
<br>
s * r * y / 6 / points<br>
<br>
What this means is that every second saved by reducing cast time, means more time for you to meditate.  The 6 represents 6 seconds/tick.  So lets say we have Deftness3 and we're chain casting Transon's Elemental Infusion(level 52) and medding inbetween cast times.  5 * 0.25 * 4 / 6 = 0.833FT while casting beneficial spells, at a pretty steep cost of 0.069 FT/point.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Spell Casting Fury</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> - kind of an odd one<br>
This, like mastery, depends on a certain amount per minute - this time damage.  It's kind of complicated =p<br>
<br>
(1 - (1 / (1 + (damage modifier)*(crit percentage)))) * (mana / damage) * (damage*frequency/ 10 ticks) / points<br>
<br>
Damage modifier for fury1 is 0.33, fury2 = 0.67, fury3 = 1.00  Crit percentages are 2%, 4%, 7% for each respective level of fury.<br>
<br>
The first part of the equation calculates the percentage of &quot;free damage&quot; generated by various levels of Casting Fury, and how much mana it would have cost to produce that damage.  Mana / damage is just the amount of mana a spell cost (times by (1-x) if you want to account for mastery/specialization).  Damage * frequency / 10 ticks is the ammount of damage per minute.  Lets say we're casting SoFB five times a minute, with no focus bracer, to keep things a little simpler with Fury3.  1 - (1 / (1 + 1.00*0.07) = 0.065<br>
0.065 * (334 / 1005) * (5 * 1005 / 10) = 0.065 * 0.332 * 502.5 = 10.855FT and creating a pretty good 0.905 FT/point.  Fury1 works out to only 0.091 FT/point though - so do it all the way!<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Mend Companion</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
This analysis doesn't account for the amount of time saved should the skill save you from having to remake a whole new pet...or find a rez <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
(1980 / normal heal amount) * ((normal heal cost)*(1-x) + y*(s*(1-r))) / 1440 ticks / 5 points<br>
<br>
normal heal amount is 580 for 52 pet heal, 900 for 60 pet heal. Their respective mana costs are 275 and 400.  1440 ticks is the recast time on Mend.<br>
The equation takes into account mana lost by the time it would take to heal the pet the same amount that Mend does instantly(I assume it's instant).<br>
Using the 52 pet heal, with x of 11%, y of 4, r of 15% we get <br>
3.414 * (244.75 + 4*(5*0.85)) / 1440 = 0.621FT or 0.124FT/point.  3.414 is basically the number of heals needed to equal 1980 points healed by Mend.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Quick Summoning</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
This is basically the same as Deftness - it mostly likely will apply for long CoH or mod-rod pile making sessions.  It calculates the extra mana gained by sitting during the time saved by being able to cast quicker.<br>
<br>
s * r * y / 6 / points<br>
<br>
At max QS, casting CoHs and medding inbetween, you get FT4, or 0.22FT/point.  However if we take into account the difference between QS2 and 3, wearing a Naki ring, the last 9 points spent on QS3 are only worth about 0.088 per point.<br>
<br>
So, if I haven't made too many mistakes, or bored you to death, quick summary:<br>
<br>
Spell Casting Mastery 1-3 = 0.33-4.0FT/point<br>
Innate Regeneration = 0.247FT/point at any level<br>
Mental Clarity 1 = 0.5FT/point<br>
Mental Clarity 1-2 = 0.33FT/point<br>
Mental Clarity 1-3 = 0.25FT/point<br>
Mental Clarity 3 = 0.167FT/point<br>
Spell Casting Fury 1-3 = 0.905FT/point<br>
Spell Deftness 1 = 0.083FT/point<br>
Spell Deftness 1-3 = 0.069FT/point<br>
Mend Companion = 0.124FT/point<br>
Quick Summoning 1-3 = 0.22FT/point during CoH, 0.083 making modrods.<br>
Quick Summoning 3 = 0.088FT/point<br>
<br>
A lot of the numbers change depending on the spells your casting, and whether you have SoA.  Plus having some skills changes others - such as Deftness lowers Mend Companion slightly, but Deftness and Quick Summoning can up Spell Casting Mastery by letting you spend more mana per minute.<br>
<br>
